{"lemma":"مَعْزُ","slug":"مَعْزُ","root":"م.ع.ز","root_slug":"م-ع-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/م-ع-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَعْز","root":"معز","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38738"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%B2%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"active participle of أَعَزَّ (ʔaʕazza)","tags":["active","form-iv","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"passive participle of أَعَزَّ (ʔaʕazza)","tags":["form-iv","form-of","participle","passive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"goats","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-West Semitic *maʕaz-. Compare Arabic عَنْز (ʕanz, “goat”), from Proto-Semitic *ʕVnz- (“goat”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38738","headword_ar":"مَعْزٌ","root":"mEz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEazN","text_ar":"مَعَزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) gen. ns., (S, Msb,) [or rather quasi-pl. ns., signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Goats;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganam","text_ar":"غَنَم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaA^onN","text_ar":"ضَاْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanam","text_ar":"عَنَم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that have hair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DA^on","text_ar":"ضاْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"being those that have wool; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEozFY","text_ar":"مِعْزًى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) accord. to Sb, (S,) with tenween, (S, Msb,) when indeterminate, (Msb,) and perfectly decl., (S,) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"] being a letter of quasicoördination, not a characteristic of the fem. gender, (S, Msb,) for the word is quasi-coördinate to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dirohamN","text_ar":"دِرْهَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolalN","text_ar":"فِعْلَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"of quasi-coördination follows the same rules as a letter belonging to the word itself, as is shown by their saying ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEayozK","text_ar":"مُعَيْزٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urayoTK","text_ar":"اُرَيْطٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEayoziYN","text_ar":"مُعَيْزِىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urayoTiYN","text_ar":"اُرَيْطِىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as the dim. forms of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEozFY","text_ar":"مِعْزًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroTFY","text_ar":"اَرْطًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"with tenween, the letter next after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"of diminution being with kesr, like as they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"durayohimN","text_ar":"دُرَيْهِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for if the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"were to denote the fem. gender they would not change it into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEayoziYN","text_ar":"مُعَيْزِىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the original form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEayozK","text_ar":"مُعَيْزٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] like as they do not change it in the dims. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubolaY","text_ar":"حُبْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoraY","text_ar":"اَخْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubayolaY","text_ar":"حُبَيْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxayozaY","text_ar":"اُخَيْزَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) it is sometimes made fem., [by being written or pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEozaApN","text_ar":"مِعْزَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and sometimes it is made imperfectly decl. [and therefore without tenween]: (K:) Fr says, that it is [itself] fem., but that some make it masc. [and therefore with tenween]: but A 'Obeyd says, that most of the Arabs pronounce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iforaY","text_ar":"ذِفْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"without tenween, while some of them pronounce it with tenween, whereas all of them pronounce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEozFY","text_ar":"مِعْزًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"with tenween: (S:) IAar says, that it is perfectly decl. when likened to the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mifoEalN","text_ar":"مِفْعَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and imperfectly decl. when held to accord. with the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolaY","text_ar":"فِعْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) accord. to Aboo-'Amr, Ibn-El-'Alà, it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEazN","text_ar":"مَعَزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiza","text_ar":"مَعِزَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iforaY","text_ar":"ذِفْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*afarN","text_ar":"ذَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, S:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiyzN","text_ar":"مَعِيزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEozN","text_ar":"مَعْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) or is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEozN","text_ar":"مَعْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or rather a quasi-pl. n.] like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabiydN","text_ar":"عَبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umoEuwzN","text_ar":"اُمْعُوزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEozN","text_ar":"مَعْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and so are ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEaAzN","text_ar":"مِعَازٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEozaA='N","text_ar":"مِعْزَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sgh, K:) [respecting"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umoEuwzN","text_ar":"اُمْعُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see also below:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEozN","text_ar":"مَعْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as well as its syns. mentioned above, like all quasi-pl. ns., is sometimes masc., but generally] is fem.: (Msb:) a male is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAEizN","text_ar":"مَاعِزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) and so a female; (Msb, K;) or a female is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAEizapN","text_ar":"مَاعِزَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, TA) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEozapN","text_ar":"مَعْزَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aroqaA='u","text_ar":"شَرْقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEozaAp","text_ar":"مِعْزَاة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN mina AlmaEozi","text_ar":"شَاةٌ مِنَ المَعْزِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is also used as a sing., (Msb,) and is applied to a male and to a female: (Msb, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wh","text_ar":"شوه"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaboYN","text_ar":"ظَبْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoEuzN","text_ar":"اَمْعُزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. [of pauc.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEozN","text_ar":"مَعْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEobudN","text_ar":"اَعْبُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabodN","text_ar":"عَبْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAEizN","text_ar":"مَاعِزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAEizapN","text_ar":"مَاعِزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawaAEizu","text_ar":"مَوَاعِزُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEaAzN","text_ar":"مِعَازٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umoEuwzN","text_ar":"اُمْعُوزٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are said to be quasi-pl. ns. (TA.) The goats of the Arabs of the desert have short hair, not long enough to be spun; but the goats of the cold countries, and of the people of the fertile regions, have abundant hair, and of this the Akrád [or Kurds] fabricate their tents. (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadomuriY~N","text_ar":"تَدْمُرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dmr","text_ar":"دمر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAy^inN","text_ar":"ضَايِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DA^n","text_ar":"ضان"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA","As","Sgh"]}]}}